-- Dubai's Emaar aims to float Egyptian unit in June 2015 -chairman
-- By Matt Smith and Sagarika Jaisinghani
-- Thu Oct 02, 2014 08:51AM EDT
-- None



DUBAI, Oct 2 (Reuters) - Dubai's Emaar Properties <EMAR.DU> hopes to launch an initial public offering of its Egyptian unit in about June 2015, the company's chairman told a conference in Dubai on Thursday.

Mohamed Alabbar said the Egyptian unit was worth between 3 billion dirhams and 4 billion dirhams ($816.8 million-$1.09 billion).